= Cherry

  http://tigerops.org

Cherry is xml/xhtml templating system. Cherry provides 100% sepearation between
logic and presentation.

Cherry is a "weaving" template system that can operate on the back-end
via Ruby or on the front-end via Javascript/jQuery off-loading
some of the back-end work load, while also providing 100% SOC
(Seperation of Concern).

== Examples

Here is an exampl of usage in Javascript.

   data = {
     hello: "Hello, World!"
   }

   $.cherry(data)

Cherry templates are especially useful when filled via AJAX with JSON data.
For this reason a shortcut is provided.

  $.cherry_ajax('http://somewhere/data.json')

